cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.SD (Sound): The paper focuses on speaker recognition from audio data, which falls under the sound category.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper uses Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for speaker recognition, which is a common technique in natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the computation and language category.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper develops and compares different CNN models and training strategies for speaker recognition, which falls under the machine learning category.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper also uses visual data (i.e. videos) to collect the audio data, which falls under the computer vision category.
- cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with audio-visual data and speaker recognition, which falls under the multimedia category.
